The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) Wednesday arraigned five persons before a Federal High Court in Lagos, over alleged illegal deal in petroleum products. The defendants MV Tim Begele, Ukwuoma Ahamefula, Nelson Omeogor, Evans Efemuaya, and Jude Eghreriniovo are arraigned before the court on a three-count charge of conspiracy, unlawful deal and attempt to unlawfully export petroleum products. The defendants, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge. After their pleas, defence counsel, Mr Peter Atabor, informed the court that he had just seen the charge and would file the necessary bail applications. The court consequently, adjourned the case until April 1 and ordered that the defendants be remanded in the correctional Service pending bail. According to the charge, the defendants were said to have committed the offences on Dec. 3, 2019. They were said to have conspired to deal in about 3,911 metric tonnes of petroleum products without appropriate licence. EFCC also alleged that the defendants had attempted to export the tonnes of petroleum, before they were apprehended. The offences contravenes the provisions of sections 1, 1(17) , and 1(19) of the Miscellaneous offences Act Cap M17 Laws of the Federation 2004. 